    "body": "@CarterLi - we did announce the plans to remove `let-env` more than three weeks ago, and also reached out to third-party tools to make sure they had updates. That said, I think where we could have done better is to make sure tool maintainers knew when the Nushell version without `let-env` was shipping.\r\n\r\nAs for your question about config/env: you'll also need to remove your config/env files that were compatible with the older Nushell version and have Nushell regenerate them for you. After you do that, you should be back to a working state.\r\n\r\nIf you have specific Nushell questions/concerns please file them on the [Nushell repo](https://github.com/nushell/nushell).",
